race.comment: THEBLADE (9) had a 46-day break before his game effort over this distance at Rosehill last start where he led until the concluding stages of the race won by GOLDEN STRAAND. Strips fitter and drops 3.5kgs. Sure to give backers a great sight. MIDNIGHT DYNAMITE (4) was there to pounce last time out over this trip but didn't quite finish off in that GOLDEN STRAAND race. Fitter for two runs back and a tongue tie going on may be see a spike in form. EDITING (2) returns from a 19-week lay-off. Bolted in first-up at Doomben last prep then wound up the campaign two runs later with a 1.2 length defeat in the Group 3 Fred Best. Lightly raced mare who could easily blow this field away if she is forward enough. GOLDEN STRAAND (5) defeated a couple of today's key rivals at Rosehill over this distance a fortnight ago. Sparingly raced entire with plenty more to offer. Likely leader JUST GLAMOUROUS (6) resumes and looks the only other realistic winning hope.
